issues.description:
As a recruiter, when I visit a candidate profile for a candidate with a valid email address then I can see the two-way email task in the sliding side panel in the correct order, with the correct icon and tooltip as per the figma.

 

[https://www.figma.com/design/HpAOHGAeXBORpHnyhsCMja/2-Way-Email_Recruiting_12_2024?node-id=6887-23498&t=aEfWMKPzAsiV95bP-0] 
h2. Scenarios:

{color:#4c9aff}*Scenario 1 - Email Task is visible*{color}

{*}Given{*}: {color:#172b4d}there is a candidate with a primary home email and job application and the processing user has view access to the new email domain and the other side panel tasks are visible (candidate notes, job application notes, sms and whatsapp){color}

{*}When{*}: I view the candidate profile

{color:#172b4d}{*}Then{*}: I see the Conversational Email task in the side panel, with the correct icon and tooltip and the task is after notes and before sms{color}

 

{color:#4c9aff}*Scenario 2 - Email Task is masked for masked candidate*{color}

{*}Given{*}: I am on the candidate profile where the email task is visible and viewing a job application which is masked for me as a user

{color:#172b4d}{*}When{*}: I click on the email task{color}

{color:#172b4d}{*}Then{*}: the panel opens and I see the masked conversation message and graphic (Conversation hidden for masked job application - same text as sms and whatsapp){color}

 

{color:#4c9aff}*Scenario 3 - One masked view is visible for all three conversation tasks*{color}

{*}Given{*}: I am on the candidate profile where the email, sms and whatsapp tasks are visible and viewing a job application which is masked for me as a user

{color:#172b4d}{*}When{*}: I view the side panel{color}

{color:#172b4d}{*}Then{*}: I only see one icon with the masked icon representing all three conversations are masked{color}

 

{color:#172b4d}{*}Notes{*}:{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}For New Items Count - we can use HRI as it is today but this may need to be changed later {color}
 * {color:#172b4d}Coffeehouse branch with part of the code - emily.oregan/emailSpike{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}Do we need to check Messaging SKU? - no, the{color}he Messaging SKU will *not* be required to use 2-way email (confirmed by Tashin and Restine from OE PM)

 

*How to test masking:*

You can configure what stages the job applications will be masked in and which security groups they should be masked for with the task - *Maintain Masked Recruiting Configurations,* 
*2997$16975*
Then you can use the task *Maintain Masked Job Requisition Defaults,* 
*2997$17078*
 to configure rules for which job requisitions should have masking applied to them.

Then click the 'Default All Job Requisitions' button on this task to apply the masking.

Now if you log in as a user who has masking applied and view a job application that is for a job requisition matching the masking rules you'll see the masking.

 
